# Access-MCP Cursor Rules

## Project Context

You are working with Access-MCP, an MCP server for Microsoft Access databases.
When the Access-MCP server is connected, you have tools to interact with Access databases.

## Access Database Conventions

- Always open the database (`Session_OpenDatabase`) before using any other tools
- Always close the database (`Session_CloseDatabase`) when done to release file locks
- Read schema and VBA before making modifications
- Use parameterized queries for user-supplied values

## Access SQL Syntax

- Wildcards: use `*` not `%` in LIKE patterns
- Date literals: `#2024-01-15#`
- Booleans: `True`/`False` or `-1`/`0`
- Top N: `SELECT TOP 10 * FROM Table` (no LIMIT)
- Conditional: `IIf(condition, true_val, false_val)` not `IF()`
- Crosstab: `TRANSFORM ... SELECT ... PIVOT`

## VBA Standards

- `Option Explicit` at top of every module
- Error handling: `On Error GoTo ErrHandler`
- Form controls: `Me.ControlName`
- Actions: `DoCmd.OpenForm`, `DoCmd.RunSQL`, etc.
- Domain functions: `DLookup`, `DCount`, `DSum`

## File Types

- `.accdb` — Access 2007+ database (preferred)
- `.mdb` — Access 97-2003 database (legacy)
- `.adp` — Access Data Project (SQL Server frontend)
- `.laccdb` / `.ldb` — Lock files (never commit these)
